Head teachers warn of chaos in the more than 23,000 public primary schools with an estimated more than 12 million pupils.On Monday, the primary school heads said they should be allowed to have pupils in session in shifts. Head teachers have cautioned schools are ill-prepared to reopen next Monday, citing congestion in primary schools and warning of chaos if funds are not provided urgently to enable necessary precautions.
And should schools reopen as scheduled, they want primary schools allowed to adopt a shift system to ensure compliance with strict health protocols on social distancing to curb the spread of coronavirus.



