Prof Magoha stated that no candidate should be sent from school due to lack of school fees.
“The candidates whose schools were closed due to adverse effects of Covid-19 pandemic will all be absorbed in public schools and assigned examination centres by the Kenya National Examination Council (Knec),” he said.
Additional reporting by Victor Raballa The CS called on parents who can afford to go ahead and buy masks for their children. KPSA estimates that close to 300 institutions will not open on January 4, affecting 56,000 children. The National Treasury has revised the tax bands for salaried workers. Prof Magoha said no child should be denied admission because of unpaid fees for the first term or second term. The national government has not hidden its intent to control the capital city.